  "prompt": "How does GiftCardMall.com make money?",
  "response": "GiftCardMall.com primarily makes money through several channels:\n\n1. **Retail Partnerships:** GiftCardMall.com partners with various retailers and brands to offer a wide selection of gift cards. They earn a commission or fee from these partners for every gift card sold on their platform.\n\n2. **Service Fees:** In some cases, GiftCardMall.com may charge service fees on certain transactions, such as for gift card delivery, processing, or activation.\n\n3. **Corporate Sales:** They sell bulk gift cards to businesses that use them for incentives, rewards, or promotional purposes, often at a discount but still profitable due to volume.\n\n4. **Marketing and Promotions:** GiftCardMall.com might collaborate with retailers for marketing and promotional activities. They can charge retailers for better placement and visibility on their website or for inclusion in special promotions.\n\nBy leveraging these revenue streams, GiftCardMall.com monetizes its platform effectively and continues to operate successfully in the gift card industry.",
